                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6091.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The fighting seems to be conducted in violation of the rules of civilized
                    warfare, as no notice has been given to noncombatants in fighting zone. The
                    direction of firing is indiscreet. The Consulate General has been rendered
                    uninhabitable and the Consul General and his staff have repaired to this
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
